Police have arrested two men in connection with an armed robbery at a Spur restaurant in Brackenfell. CAPE TOWN - Police have arrested two men in connection with an armed robbery at a Spur restaurant in Brackenfell. One was apprehended in Eerste River on Monday.A second suspect, a 30-year-old man, was detained in Khayelitsha earlier on Tuesday. The men allegedly robbed the restaurant in Old Paarl Road on Sunday evening.The police's Noloyiso Rwexana says a third suspect is yet to be found. Information was followed up after the robbery and police officers obtained three video footage which purported to show the vehicles that were used during the robbery. This led to the arrest of the two suspects. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)